NAME:
   flight desktop kill - Terminate an interactive desktop session

USAGE:
   flight desktop kill [options] <name> 

CATEGORY:
   Sessions

DESCRIPTION:
   Instruct an active interactive desktop session to terminate.

   The <name> parameter should specify the session's name, use 'flight desktop
   list' to see a list of your sessions.

OPTIONS:
   --format FORMAT  use specified FORMAT for the output (pretty, json). (default: "pretty")
   --help, -h       show help

GLOBAL OPTIONS:
   --log-level LEVEL  set the log LEVEL (debug, info, warn, error, fatal). Default: warn
